OL,3,CFirst official portrait of King
OL,4,CCharles unveiled
OL,6,F"When I started this project, His
OL,7,FMajesty The King was still His Royal
OL,8,FHighness The Prince of Wales, and much
OL,9,Flike the butterfly I've painted
OL,10,Fhovering over his shoulder, this
OL,11,Fportrait has evolved as the subject's
OL,12,Frole in our public life has
OL,13,Ftransformed," Mr Yeo said in a
OL,14,Fstatement.
OL,16,F"My aim was also to make reference to
OL,17,Fthe traditions of Royal portraiture,
OL,18,Fbut in a way that reflects a 21st
OL,19,FCentury Monarchy and, above all else,
OL,20,Fto communicate the subject's deep
OL,21,Fhumanity."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G4/7
